bib_record.title: Studies of the (d,a) reaction on N-14 in the deuteron energy range from 1 to 2.5 MeV.

free_txt: The alpha particles were detected by a
semiconductor spectrometer with a resolving power
better than 1% for 210Po alpha particles. The
spectrometer consisted  of a semiconductor detector of
the type ORTEC (200 A-40) having a linear sensitivity
to alpha particles in the energy range up to 10 MeV,
together with low noise ORTEC amplifier type 201.
Both solid and gas targets were used.
The solid target was prepared by evaporating
dimethyle glyoxeme (CH3CNOH)2 onto a silver backing
1.0 mu-m thick. Air which filled the chamber served as
the gas target, the pressure inside the chamber being
such that the thickness of the gas target did not
exceed 10 keV. The thickness of the solid target
reached 50 keV for the deuteron energy 2 MeV.
